The paper deals with lifting theorems, which are a fundamental concept in communication complexity and computational complexity theory. The paper focuses on gadgets with low discrepancy, which is a concept that is closely related to combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also deals with logarithmic-size gadgets, which are relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper's results are likely to be of interest to researchers in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS).
